orts that \nthe patient had difficulty focusing attention, was easily distracted, or had difficulty keeping track of what was \nsaid AND the inattention varied or if information sources disagree in assessing level of attention. \n\n\u2022  Dash is a valid response for this item. \n\no  A dash indicates \u201cno information.\u201d CMS expects dash use to be a rare occurrence. \n\nExamples", "type": "Document"}}